Given your background and the fact that you're interviewing/networking for an Open Banking Product role, I would focus less on memorizing product frameworks and more on positioning yourself as someone who can drive business outcomes, data strategy, AI innovation, and cross-functional execution.

1. Be Ready for the "Tell Me About Yourself" Story (2 minutes)

A concise version:

> "I've spent my career at financial institutions in data, analytics, AI, and product-adjacent leadership roles. Currently I lead AI initiatives for Workplace Solutions and Client Performance, while also serving as AI controls and governance lead for the CTO organization. Before that, I was a Data Product Owner in Asset & Wealth Management, focused on areas such as fees and collateral management.

What attracts me to Open Banking is that it's transforming how customers securely share and benefit from their financial data. It sits at the intersection of APIs, data, customer experience, regulation, and innovation—areas where I have significant experience and where I believe AI can create meaningful value."



2. Know What a Product Head Wants to Assess

They will likely evaluate:

Strategic thinking

Customer obsession

Ability to influence without authority

Execution capability

Comfort with ambiguity

Understanding of Open Banking ecosystem

Leadership presence


3. Prepare for These Likely Questions

Why Open Banking?

> Open Banking is one of the most important shifts in financial services. It enables customers to control their data while creating opportunities for better financial experiences. I see a chance to combine my experience in data, AI, governance, and financial services to build products with direct customer impact.



Why are you moving from AI/Data into Product?

> Much of my work already involves product thinking—understanding customer problems, prioritizing solutions, aligning stakeholders, measuring outcomes, and driving adoption. Moving into product allows me to own the end-to-end customer and business outcome more directly.



What would your first 90 days look like?

1. Understand customers and partners.


2. Learn the existing platform, APIs, consent flows, and metrics.


3. Build relationships across engineering, risk, legal, compliance, and business teams.


4. Identify one or two high-impact opportunities that can be delivered quickly.



4. Have Strong Questions for the Product Head

These often matter as much as your answers.

Strategy

What are the top three objectives for the Open Banking organization over the next 12 months?

How do you measure success?

Where do you see the biggest opportunities and risks?


Customer

What customer problem are you most focused on solving right now?

What feedback are you hearing from fintech partners?


Execution

What are the biggest obstacles preventing faster delivery?

How do product, engineering, and risk teams work together?


AI (your differentiator)

Where do you see AI creating value within Open Banking?

Are there opportunities to improve consent experiences, developer support, fraud detection, or customer education using AI?


